The paper discusses the security aspects of mobile applications in an enterprise setup, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also talks about the development of mobile applications, which can be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE). The focus on mobility in the enterprise framework suggests that it could also be classified under mobile computing (cs.MOB). The paper also discusses the approach that can be taken at the application layer, which could fall under the category of system and information theory (cs.SI). Finally, the paper talks about reducing risk to enterprises, which could be classified under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
